Later in development, we walked away from the traditional fishermen’s village for Sweethaven and it became this bigger city with a mix of art nouveau, Miami-like beach resort and casinos. This is my take around that idea.
From Popeye’s unproduced feature, 2013. .
. .
.

Let’s go back to Sweethaven, Popeye’s village. This take was the typical fisherman’s village with wooden houses, version that was abandoned in later versions as I’ll show in coming posts. 
This was actually my very first assignment and picture on the project, at the end of 2012. (This is pretty old now and it shows...)
Pencil on paper with some photoshop enhancements.
.

Before the pirates were adults and even aviators, the first idea was that they would be a bunch of kids and teenagers living together like gypsies, clothed and equipped with things they would make, find or steal.
Again, they are drawn in a sort of Fleisher style.
From Popeye’s unproduced feature film, 2013. .
.

A later version of the pirate’s village. The idea was that they would be have a little village made out of colourful gypsy caravans hidden in caves, attached to the walls, etc... That was some exploration around that idea. 
Not too happy about this painting, it looks a bit old now, but that was still a fun concept. 
From Popeye’s unproduced feature, 2013.
.

My best nine for 2019. 
Making me think that I should continue the shameful memories comics. I wrote a bunch but I simply lack the time to do them. Would you guys like to read more of them?
Anyway, thank you for your continuous support and welcome to all the new subscribers!
.

The pirates HQ. This version was a direct reference/hommage to Porco Rosso’s hidden beach.
The village would be hidden in a hollow Island, they would fly in a cavity through the waterfall, and get to the village. The last quick roughs explore this idea.
Pencil on paper, from the unproduced Popeye feature. 2013.
.
.

Pirate ship development. The idea was that they would have tuned a reclaimed tug boat and improve it to make a sort of floating village. The two last ones are just the idea pushed further and an idea with shipment containers.
From Popeye’s unproduced feature, 2013.
.
